text.section:
A person who sells or offers to sell a fine print shall disclose the following information:
The year when printed and the name of the artist;
Whether the print is a part of a limited edition and, if it is:
The authorized maximum number of numbered or signed prints, or both, in the edition;
The authorized maximum number of unnumbered or unsigned prints, or both, in the edition;
Any authorized maximum number of artist's, publisher's, printer's or other proofs, exclusive of trial proofs, outside the regular edition; and
The total size of the edition;
Whether the plate has been destroyed, effaced, altered, defaced, or canceled after the current edition;
If there were any prior plates of the same master image:
The total number of plates; and
A designation of the plate from which the print was taken;
If there were any prior or later editions from the same plate:
The series number of the edition of which the print is a part; and
The aggregate size of all other editions;
Whether the edition is a posthumous edition or restrike and, if it is, whether the plate has been reworked; and
The name of any workshop where the edition was printed.
